🌱 EcoSched-xv6
An enhanced version of the xv6 that introduces environment-aware scheduling.

🚀 Overview
EcoSched-xv6 monitors simulated temperature and power usage, converts them into a system state, and adapts CPU scheduling accordingly.

⚙️ Features
Sensor System: User-space processes simulate environmental data via custom syscalls
Sustainability Monitor: Kernel maps data → NORMAL, ECO, CRITICAL
Eco-Aware Scheduler: Scheduling adapts based on system state
Eco-Credits: Processes gain/lose credits based on CPU efficiency

🛠️ Run
make clean
make
make qemu

🎯 Concept
Environmental state → influences scheduler → rewards efficient processes
